  "prompt": "What is the best open-source captive portal for a WiFi Hospot?",
  "response": "Several open-source captive portal solutions are popular for WiFi hotspots:\n\n1. CoovaChilli\n- Lightweight and flexible\n- Supports RADIUS authentication\n- Part of the Coova project\n- Good for small to medium deployments\n\n2. pfSense Captive Portal\n- Integrated with pfSense firewall\n- User-friendly web interface\n- Support for multiple authentication methods\n- Scalable and robust\n\n3. WiFiDog\n- Lightweight and modular\n- Supports multiple authentication backends\n- Good for custom, flexible implementations\n- Active community support\n\n4. NoDogSplash\n- Simple and lightweight\n- Easy configuration\n- Good for basic captive portal needs\n- Low resource consumption\n\n5. OpenNDS\n- Feature-rich\n- Supports multiple authentication methods\n- Active development\n- Flexible configuration options\n\n6. FreeRADIUS\n- Powerful RADIUS server\n- Can be combined with other solutions\n- Highly scalable\n- Extensive authentication options\n\nRecommendation depends on:\n- Scale of deployment\n- Required features\n- Technical complexity\n- Performance needs\n- Authentication requirements\n\nFor most small to medium deployments, pfSense or CoovaChilli are solid choices.",
